  .privacy-intro
    %p We value your privacy. We will never sell your personal information outside of what you allow through normal use of the site.
    %br/
    If you visit the site:
    %ul
      %li We may collect data like your IP address and other server logging info that helps us run the site smoothly and efficiently
      %li We may collect aggregate data that doesn't personally identify you that we may share with trusted partners and third parties
    In addition, if you take action on the site:
    %ul
      %li We may make public information like your name, city, state, and comments as part of your signing of a petition, RSVPing for an event, or the like
      %li We will email you "transactional" email related to actions you take on the site (ex: sending a thank you email after you sign a petition or sending action alerts), from which you can unsubscribe at any time
      %li We may send mass email updates on new projects, from which you can unsubscribe at any time
    This summary is qualified in its entirety by the Legal Terms below, which shall govern your use of the site.

